1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,560
Hello everyone and welcome to another great lesson here at EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod的另一堂精彩课程。

2
00:00:07,560 --> 00:00:08,700
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:08,700 --> 00:00:13,360
My name is Catherine and today we've got an upper intermediate level lesson for you all.
我是Catherine，今天我们为大家准备了一节中高级课程。

4
00:00:13,360 --> 00:00:14,360
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:19,640
We're going to talk a little bit about business and specifically we are in a business meeting
我们要聊一点关于商务的话题，具体来说，我们正在开一个商务会议，

6
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:22,200
where we're trying to sell something to someone.
试图向某人推销东西。

7
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,200
That's right.
没错。

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:28,840
So you're going to hear a lot of talk about chocolate or in this case gourmet bonbons.
所以你会听到很多关于巧克力，或者更准确地说，是高级夹心巧克力的讨论。

9
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:29,840
Gourmet bonbons.
高级夹心巧克力。

10
00:00:29,840 --> 00:00:32,760
This is another word for chocolate candies or candies.
这是巧克力糖果的另一种说法。

11
00:00:32,760 --> 00:00:33,760
Okay.
好的。

12
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,600
So a bonbon is kind of like round usually, right?
所以bonbon通常是圆形的，对吧？

13
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:37,600
Usually, yes.
通常是的。

14
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,600
Okay.
好的。

15
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:39,600
All right.
行。

16
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,720
So let's get started and listen to today's dialogue.
那我们开始吧，听今天的对话。

17
00:00:40,720 --> 00:00:50,000
We'll be back in a moment.
我们一会儿就回来。

18
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,200
I'm glad you could find time to meet with me, Mr. Johnson.
很高兴您能抽出时间见我，约翰逊先生。

19
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:56,320
I can't think of a nicer environment for our meeting today.
我想不出比这更适合我们今天会议的环境了。

20
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:58,360
The ambience here is lovely.
这里的气氛真不错。

21
00:00:58,360 --> 00:00:59,440
No problem.
没问题。

22
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:02,760
If possible, I always combine business with pleasure.
如果可能的话，我总是把工作和娱乐结合起来。

23
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:05,640
Now let's hear more about these chocolates you're offering.
现在让我们多听听你提供的这些巧克力吧。

24
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:10,640
Well, as you know, I have recently become the sole distributor for Granger's gourmet
嗯，如你所知，我最近成为了格兰杰美食

25
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:13,280
bonbons here in the United States.
夹心巧克力在美国的独家经销商。

26
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:17,640
They're a new manufacturer and are looking to break into the luxury market.
他们是一家新制造商，正试图打入奢侈品市场。

27
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:20,840
Naturally, your restaurant sprang into my mind immediately.
自然，我立刻就想到了你的餐厅。

28
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:26,080
I think your brand exemplifies many of the same traits as Granger's and serving these
我认为你的品牌体现了许多与格兰杰相同的特质，提供这些

29
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:32,000
chocolates would really add to your reputation for providing elegant, luxurious, first-class
巧克力真的能提升你提供优雅、奢华、一流

30
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,000
dining.
餐饮的声誉。

31
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Hmm.
嗯。

32
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,160
Sounds interesting.
听起来挺有意思。

33
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:36,760
Gourmet chocolates.
美食巧克力。

34
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:37,760
Where are they produced?
它们是在哪里生产的？

35
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:38,760
Belgium?
比利时？

36
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:41,440
Actually, the factory is located in Scotland.
实际上，工厂位于苏格兰。

37
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:42,440
Really?
真的吗？

38
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:46,480
I didn't think they were known for their luxury chocolate production.
我没想到他们以生产奢侈巧克力而闻名。

39
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:49,980
That's what makes this such a fantastic opportunity.
这正是为什么这是一个绝佳的机会。

40
00:01:49,980 --> 00:01:56,040
The government is 100% supportive of creating new export markets and has guaranteed a low
政府百分之百支持开拓新的出口市场，并已保证低

41
00:01:56,040 --> 00:02:00,600
tariff for all wholesale orders of over 1,000 units.
所有超过1000件批发订单的关税。

42
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:03,800
They've also reduced the red tape involved at customs as well.
他们还简化了海关的繁琐手续。

43
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:06,360
Here, I brought these especially for you.
来，我特意给你带了这些。

44
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,360
Try one.
尝一个。

45
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,360
Oh, thanks.
哦，谢谢。

46
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,360
Hmm.
嗯。

47
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,360
Hmm.
嗯。

48
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,360
Creamy texture.
口感细腻。

49
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:12,360
Very smooth.
非常顺滑。

50
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,360
Unique, aren't they?
很独特，对吧？

51
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:17,920
I bet you've never tasted anything like it.
我敢说你从没尝过这样的味道。

52
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:22,320
Quality is assured as I personally visit the factory to make sure no one's cutting corners
质量有保证，因为我亲自去工厂检查，确保没人偷工减料

53
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:23,920
with the ingredients.
在原料上。

54
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:26,840
Only the creme de la creme make it through inspection.
只有最顶尖的才能通过检验。

55
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:27,840
Yes.
是的。

56
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,840
Very interesting flavors.
味道很有趣。

57
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:29,840
Slightly spicy.
有点辣。

58
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,840
Hmm.
嗯。

59
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:33,120
Very unique, that's for sure.
确实很独特。

60
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:35,360
Exactly what are the ingredients?
具体是什么原料？

61
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:41,360
I have it on highest authority that this traditional secret recipe has been handed down in the
我得到最高权威的消息，这个传统秘方已经传下来了

62
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:43,640
Granger family for generations.
在格兰杰家族世代相传。

63
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:46,680
I'm sure you can keep a secret.
我相信你能保守秘密。

64
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:52,840
Buttermilk, cacao beans, sugar, and haggis.
酪乳、可可豆、糖，还有哈吉斯。

65
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:55,960
What's haggis?
哈吉斯是什么？

66
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:58,360
It's a traditional Scottish delicacy.
这是一种传统的苏格兰美食。

67
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:04,560
You take sheep's liver, heart, and lung and stuff it inside the sheep's stomach.
你把羊肝、羊心和羊肺塞进羊胃里。

68
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:09,280
I'll get back to you.
我回头再联系你。

69
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,280
Mr. Johnson.
约翰逊先生。

70
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,280
Mr. Johnson.
约翰逊先生。

71
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,280
All right.
好吧。

72
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,280
We're back.
我们回来了。

73
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:22,600
So a lot of interesting vocab there.
所以那里有很多有趣的词汇。

74
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:27,000
The guy was trying to convince them about these chocolates but it turned out to be something
那家伙试图说服他们这些巧克力很好，但结果却是有点

75
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,040
a little bit strange and we'll talk about that in a little while.
奇怪的东西，我们稍后会讨论这个。

76
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:35,600
Before we get into that, why don't we take a look at seven key words that we have prepared
在我们进入正题之前，不如先看看我们今天为你们准备的七个关键词

77
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:40,000
for you today on Language Takeaway.
在“语言小贴士”环节。

78
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Language Takeaway.
语言小贴士。

79
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Okay.
好的。

80
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,600
So we've divided Language Takeaway into two parts today.
所以今天我们把“语言小贴士”分成两部分。

81
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:49,320
The first part is all about business and manufacturing.
第一部分全是关于商业和制造业的。

82
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:50,680
So what's our first word, Marco?
那么，马可，我们的第一个词是什么？

83
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:51,680
All right.
好的。

84
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:56,600
So I talked about being the sole distributor for this company called Granger's Gourmet
所以我提到了我是这家叫格兰杰美食的公司的独家经销商。

85
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,600
Bonbons.
夹心巧克力。

86
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,600
Okay.
好的。

87
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,600
A distributor.
经销商。

88
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:00,600
Okay.
好的。

89
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:07,880
This is a person or a company and the distributor is someone who distributes or sells a product,
经销商是指一个人或一家公司，负责分销或销售产品。

90
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:08,880
right?
对吧？

91
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:09,880
Right.
对。

92
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:10,880
So the factory will make them.
所以工厂负责生产。

93
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:16,080
He will get all these goods from the factory and then he will be the one that gives it
他从工厂拿到所有货物，然后负责把这些货物送到不同的零售店。

94
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:18,720
to the different retail stores.
送到不同的零售店。

95
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:23,100
So he can have many clients and he is the main person who you get it from.
所以他可以有很多客户，他是你拿货的主要渠道。

96
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,280
So obviously they don't get it directly from the factory.
显然，他们不是直接从工厂拿货的。

97
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,280
Okay.
好的。

98
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:31,040
So this person, a distributor or a company, is in the middle of the transaction.
所以这个人，经销商或公司，处于交易的中间环节。

99
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:35,400
On one side there is the manufacturer and on the other side there is the retail market
一边是制造商，另一边是零售市场。

100
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,600
or stores.
或者商店。

101
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,600
Exactly.
没错。

102
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:41,000
And as you said, that's our second key word today, manufacturer.
正如你所说，这是我们今天的第二个关键词，制造商。

103
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Okay.
好的。

104
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:46,320
Manufacturer, again, is a person or a company that makes a good.
制造商，同样，是指生产商品的人或公司。

105
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:49,720
So for example, a television manufacturer makes TV.
比如，电视机制造商生产电视机。

106
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,360
It's like a factory.
就像工厂一样。

107
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,360
Exactly.
没错。

108
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,680
So they manufacture things.
所以他们制造东西。

109
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,680
They make them.
他们生产它们。

110
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,680
All right.
好的。

111
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:58,000
So we've got distributors who are moving goods.
所以我们有经销商在运输货物。

112
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,760
We have manufacturers who are making them.
我们有制造商在生产它们。

113
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:03,840
But what happens when we want to move a good out of a country?
但当我们想把货物运出国外时，会发生什么？

114
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:04,840
Okay.
好的。

115
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:07,960
So that is our third word for today.
这就是我们今天的第三个词。

116
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:12,960
Usually in customs, we have to pay a tariff for these goods or a tax.
通常在海关，我们必须为这些货物支付关税或税款。

117
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:13,960
Okay.
好的。

118
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:19,400
So a tariff is a special kind of tax that you pay when you are trying to export or send
所以关税是一种特殊的税，当你试图出口或把在国内生产的货物运到国外时，你需要支付。

119
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:23,000
outside of your country goods that you've made in that country.
把在国内生产的货物运到国外时。

120
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:28,800
So for example, if I make 100 TVs in America, but I want to sell these TVs to someone in
比如，如果我在美国生产了100台电视机，但我想把这些电视机卖给墨西哥的某人。

121
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:31,400
Mexico, I have to pay a tariff.
我就得支付关税。

122
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:38,760
I have to pay like $10 to the government that allows me to send these out of the country.
我得向政府支付大约10美元，才能允许我把这些货物运出国外。

123
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:39,760
That's right.
没错。

124
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,280
So that is a tariff.
这就是关税。

125
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:45,600
And now when he was talking about tariffs and how the government is reducing the tariffs
现在，当他谈到关税以及政府如何降低关税来激励商业时。

126
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:51,640
in order to motivate a business, he talked about also that the government is reducing
他还提到政府正在减少。

127
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:53,400
or cutting the red tape.
或者削减繁文缛节。

128
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,400
Okay.
好的。

129
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:58,560
So he says, listen, they've also reduced the red tape involved at customs.
所以他说，听着，他们还减少了海关的繁文缛节。

130
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:04,400
So this means that before they were encountering some problems at customs, because customs,
这意味着以前他们在海关遇到了一些问题，因为海关。

131
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:08,300
you know, there's a lot of paperwork, there's a lot of taxes, there's a lot of information
你知道，有很多文书工作，很多税款，很多信息。

132
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:10,120
you have to provide.
你必须提供。

133
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,120
It's a hassle.
很麻烦。

134
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,120
A lot of paperwork.
很多文书工作。

135
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,120
Right.
对。

136
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:17,840
So this kind of paperwork, bureaucracy, this is called red tape in English.
所以这种文书工作、官僚作风，在英语中被称为繁文缛节。

137
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:27,400
For example, I would love to get a visa for my foreign husband, but there's a lot of red
比如，我很想给我外国丈夫办签证，但有很多繁文缛节。

138
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,400
tape.
有很多工作要做。

139
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,640
There's a lot of work that we have to do.
有很多官僚程序要走。

140
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:32,320
There's a lot of bureaucratic processes that you have to do.
有很多官僚程序要走。

141
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:33,320
All right.
好的。

142
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:38,080
So red tape, this means a lot of paperwork, a lot of work that you have to do.
所以繁文缛节，意味着很多文书工作，很多你必须做的工作。

143
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,080
Okay.
好的。

144
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:42,040
So those are our key words that are related to business.
这些就是与商业相关的关键词。

145
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:45,360
Now let's move on to a couple of different adjectives.
现在我们来谈谈几个不同的形容词。

146
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:48,980
The first one, when he talked about chocolates, he said elegant.
第一个，当他谈到巧克力时，他说优雅。

147
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:50,680
He said that something is elegant.
他说某样东西很优雅。

148
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,680
Okay.
好的。

149
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,680
Elegant.
优雅。

150
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:53,680
This is a great adjective.
这是一个很棒的形容词。

151
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:58,400
You're going to see this on a lot of luxury brand items.
你会在很多奢侈品牌商品上看到它。

152
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:03,680
Elegance means something is elegant if it is classy, if it looks really good and rich.
优雅意味着某样东西如果很高级、看起来很好且奢华，就是优雅的。

153
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:09,360
Or you could say that dress is very elegant, that mink coat is very elegant.
或者你可以说那条裙子很优雅，那件貂皮大衣很优雅。

154
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,360
Okay.
好的。

155
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,400
This is a positive thing.
这是正面的评价。

156
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:14,640
So something that looks kind of expensive at times as well.
所以有时也指看起来有点贵的东西。

157
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,120
Yeah, that's right.
是的，没错。

158
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:20,640
Another word that means looking expensive or elegant is luxurious.
另一个表示看起来昂贵或优雅的词是豪华的。

159
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,680
Okay.
好的。

160
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:26,500
So luxurious comes from the noun luxury.
所以豪华的来自名词奢侈品。

161
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,500
That's right.
没错。

162
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,120
Luxury, luxurious.
豪华，奢华的。

163
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:33,760
So we can say that the executive suites at this hotel are very luxurious.
所以我们可以说这家酒店的行政套房非常奢华。

164
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:39,800
They have a jacuzzi, a king-size bed, expensive silk sheets.
它们有按摩浴缸、特大号床、昂贵的丝绸床单。

165
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,600
The best quality materials.
最优质的材料。

166
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:45,800
So you can say that elegant and luxurious kind of go hand in hand.
所以你可以说优雅和奢华是相辅相成的。

167
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,800
That's right.
没错。

